  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Inclusive Resilience to Climatic and Socio Economic Stress Effective DRM and Humanitarian Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency cash based response and technical assistance to Government to design and implement pilot shock-responsive Social Cash Transfer</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This systems strengthening programme directly targets systems and staff involved in Malawi&#x2019;s National Social Support Programme &#x2013; including Ministry of Finance, Ministry of Gender, and UN and NGO actors involved in social protection and humanitarian aid in Malawi. The ultimate beneficiaries are ultra-poor households targeted under national social protection who are also identified in Malawi Vulnerability Assessment (MVAC) as requiring Humanitarian Assistance. For 2017/18 the Programme targetted 3,500 households in in Balaka District</narrative>
  </description>
